text: I’ve been going to Drae’s Barber shop for about a year or so, and now I don’t trust anyone else to do my fade/cut my hair. If you’re looking for a skilled, and professional barbershop in Opelika, check them out. You won’t be disappointed. They’re good people! God bless.

name: D McGhee
text: Great barber shop. Here are some tips before you go. If you go without an appointment made, the wait time ranges from 15-60 minutes depending on which barber you get or have. My barber is Drae. A lot of people make an appointment which is an extra $5. So it is best to make one before going since you make have a bit of a wait when there. There are great seats  in the place so you can get comfy while you wait for your turn.
